    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>Revd</p>
			<p><addressee>I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish&#45;Hebrew</hi></add></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>July 17&#44; 1849</date>.</p>
			<p>Life and peace to my friend <addressee>Rabbi Leeser</addressee>.....</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">We have dared to go into the holy courts<lb/> of God and pray that he might grant to you&#44; whose<lb/> name is well known in Judah and <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; long life.<lb/> I have presumed to speak&#44; and send my words to<lb/> you. I have heard through <persName>Mr. Morrison</persName> that you<lb/> will be good enough to listen to my words&#44; and I<lb/> therefore gave him &#36;15 with the earnest decision&#44; <del>that</del><lb/> at the end of two months&#44; to give you more until I<lb/> complete my payments. But now <del>my</del> I am afraid<lb/> I know very well all the good you have done for me&#44;<lb/> from the beginnings to this day. And now I am in<lb/> danger of being caught in a transgression&#59; not to be<lb/> able to fulfill my promise. For the cause of the<lb/> difficulties of the time and the confusion caused by<lb/> the cholera&#44; not only has the money and means of a<lb/> livelihood decreased&#44; but there is a lack of the utmost<lb/> necessities. That is the reason why my soul weeps<lb/> in hiding and I am concerned lest&#44; much to my<lb/> regret and pain&#44; I be unable to fulfill&#44; on the<lb/> appointed day&#44; that to which I see myself ob&#45;<lb/>ligated and I should very much like to accomplish.<lb/> I am anxious that you should think bitterly of me&#44;<lb/> for he&#44; who knows the hidden secrets of the heart&#44; to him<lb/> it is clear that my thought and desire is to pay&#44;<lb/> God willing. Only one thing I ask of you&#44; to give<lb/> permission to <persName>Mr. Morrison</persName> to wait a few weeks<lb/> until the disturbance caused by the sickness<lb/> passes. For&#44; thank God&#44; I have received news from<lb/> all my customers who have for years lodged<lb/> with me&#44; to hold their rooms in readiness<lb/> for them. They expect to come&#44; at the latest&#44;</p>
		<pb n="5"/>
			<p>towards the end of <date>August</date>. And&#44; if it<lb/> will be the will of the Creator&#44; to send his<lb/> complete cure even sooner&#44; and if he will<lb/> remove his anger from us&#44; They will come<lb/> here earlier. I stretch my hand out to<lb/> you and hope<add>&#63;</add> that for God&#39;s sake you do not<lb/> judge me harshly&#44; and to extend my<lb/> term for another four to six weeks. Be&#45;<lb/>cause of this our Father in heaven will<lb/> lengthen your days and your years in<lb/> goodness and sweetness. And nay this<lb/> be this will. Amen.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My wife and sons&#44; long life to them&#44;<lb/> send you greetings&#44; and especially my<lb/> son <persName>Nathan</persName>. Etc.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">With greetings of Peace&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Your friend&#44; who waits for your aid&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;</p>
			<p>P. S. If you will honor me with an answer&#44;<lb/> it will be like cool water for a tired spirit.<lb/> My address is <persName role="author">L. Solomon</persName> <placeName>250 William St.<lb/> N.Y.</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
